  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "2414750c-f3ba-809e-9ad6-f6ae18940681",
      "heading": "Abstract",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Moment of Prediction",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "End of Course Grade",
          "Fail (1), Pass (2), Average (3), Good (4), Excellent (5)",
          "14898 course-student pairs",
          "3 Cohorts of a Software Engineering Program ",
          "Learner Grades, \nCourse Semantic Information",
          "[Course Triplets (i.e. Entity → Relation → Entity), Student Grades Matrix]",
          "Start of Semester",
          "Authors start by creating a knowledge graph:\n\n1. TextRank is used to rctract top 20 entities per course\n2. Create Triplets of Entity Relationship Entity.\n\nData is subsequently separated for holdout method: 80/10/10\n\nFrom here, the data follows 2 distinct modules: \n\nCourse Information is subjected to the TransE algorithm (meant to find courses that are similar to the one requiring prediction).\n\nLearners are filtered using collaborative filtering.\n\nThe results of these modules are fused together for prediction.",
          "C-CF, C-KM, U-CF, KN-CF",
          "Holdout Method",
          "Term 2:\n{RMSE: 1.1239 - C-KM, MAE: 0.84643 - C-KM}\n\nTerm 3:\n{RMSE: 0.9516 - KN-CF, MAE: 0.7046 - KN-CF}\n\nTerm 4:\n{RMSE: 0.9802 - KN-CF, MAE: 0.7298 - KN-CF}\n\nTerm 5:\n{RMSE: 0.9823 - KN-CF, MAE: 0.7382 - KN-CF}\n\nTerm 6:\n{RMSE: 0.8929 - KN-CF, MAE: 0.6418 - KN-CF}\n\nTerm 7:\n{RMSE: 0.9408 - KN-CF, MAE: 0.7035 - KN-CF}",
          "Authors look at the task of preddicting grade starting from a knowledge graph.\n\nThe authors explain that the features used are couse information and the student’s grade matrix.\n\nExperiment is repeated once per term. Clustering based approach starts being better for the second—term (smaller history) but is later surpassed by KN-CF at later stages in program duration.\n\nEssencially, the paper proposes that the knowledge graph into CF is a better alterrnative to Clustering, User-CF and Course-CF.",
          "- Cold Start Problem.\n\n- Holdout method implementation.\n\n- No comparison against more supervised conventional approaches (Deep Learning).\n\n- Small datasets.\n\n- Performance improvements do not seem to follow a continuum.\n\n- Requires validation on data from other institutions."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
