    {
      "id": "1b64750c-f3ba-80d0-9a0c-c33e0e962afa",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Collaboative filterming methods used to predict grades often put too much emphasys in history and not as much in contents of the course. The authors explore the ability of knowledge graphs to extract information from course descriptions and use it to predict a student’s grade. Models are evaulated using RMSE and are shown to outperform standard collaborative filtering and k-Means.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1b64750c-f3ba-80d0-9a0c-c33e0e962afa",
        "parent": {
